Name: .ac
Notes: Commonly used for academic websites, such as universities. However, .ac is not to be confused with the official academic domains used by several countries such as the United Kingdom (.ac.uk), India (.ac.in) or Indonesia (.ac.id). Also used in the accounting, consulting, and air-conditioning industries.
Registry: Ascension Island Network Information Centre (run by Internet Computer Bureau)

Name: .ad
Notes: Local trademark, trade name or citizenship required

Name: .ag
Notes: Also unofficially used by German businesses (where AG is an abbreviation of Aktiengesellschaft).

Name: .ai
Notes: Also unofficially used by tech companies specializing in AI (Artificial Intelligence).

Name: .al
Notes: Citizenship no longer required.

Name: .am
Notes: Also unofficially used by AM radio stations, podcasts or related business.

Name: .aq
Notes: Defined by the Antarctic Treaty as everything south of latitude 60°S. AQ domain names are available to government organizations who are signatories to the Antarctic Treaty and to other registrants who have a physical presence in Antarctica.

Name: .as
Notes: In some countries, like Norway and Denmark, "AS" or "A/S" is used as an abbreviation for stock-based or limited companies. Such companies will often make use of the domain. Also unofficially used by the Principality of Asturias, Spain.

Name: .au
Notes: Restrictions apply. In general, registrants must have an "Australian presence", and can be registered anywhere between 1 and 5 years. Includes Ashmore and Cartier Islands and Coral Sea Islands. Direct second-level domain registration (marketed as ".au Direct") has been made available commencing 24 March 2022.

Name: .aw
Notes: Restricted to registered Aruban companies, organisations and citizens

Name: .az
Notes: Only for Residents. Has no WHOIS-Server.

Name: .ba
Registry: University of Sarajevo - University tele-informatic Centre https://www.utic.unsa.ba https://www.nic.ba

Name: .bd
Notes: For individuals, registrant must have a valid NID. For companies, registrant must have company or trademark registered in Bangladesh.

Name: .be
Notes: Used for YouTube-related domains. Also unofficially used in the Canton of Bern, Switzerland.

Name: .bg
Notes: See also .бг (.bg in Cyrillic) for IDN ccTLD

Name: .bm
Notes: Local corporate registration required

Name: .bq
Entity: Caribbean Netherlands ( Bonaire,  Saba, and  Sint Eustatius)

Name: .br
Notes: Restricted. Registration is done under several categories (i.e.: .edu.br for higher education institutions, .gov.br for government agencies, etc.).

Name: .bt
Notes: Must have local presence in Bhutan, and valid trade license

Name: .bw
Notes: May also be used for the Province of Walloon Brabant, Wallonia, Belgium

Name: .by
Notes: Also unofficially used to denote Bayern (Bavaria), Germany

Name: .bz
Notes: Also unofficially used in the province of Bozen (or South Tyrol, see .st)

Name: .ca
Notes: Subject to Canadian Presence Requirements. Also unofficially used by some websites in the U.S. state of California.

Name: .cc
Notes: Australian territory: not to be confused with Cocos Island in Guam. Currently marketed as global domain, registration allowed worldwide, local presence not required; the domain is currently operated by eNIC, a VeriSign company.

Name: .cd
Notes: Also unofficially used for Compact disc-related domains.

Name: .cf
Notes: Also used as a free domain service to the public.

Name: .cm
Notes: A local entity / company in Cameroon is required to register a domain name.

Name: .cn
Notes:
A local company in China is required to register a domain name, or for personal registrations a valid Resident Identity Card. See ICP license for more information regarding registrations. Hong Kong and Macau also maintain TLDs.
Also unofficially used for Cartoon Network-related domains.

Name: .co
Notes: Marketed as a global domain. Anyone can register.

Name: .cv
Notes: Also unofficially used for curriculum vitae-related domains.

Name: .cx
Notes: Made infamous from Goatse.cx

Name: .de
Notes: German postal address for administrative contact (admin-c) required. Proxy registrations are allowed.

Name: .dj
Notes: Also unofficially used by disc jockeys.

Name: .ec
Notes: In Japan, "EC" is used as an acronym for "electronic commerce". Because of that, it's used unofficially by companies dedicated to provide online stores like BASE, a company that has two domains related to e-commerce: "base.in" and "official.ec".

Name: .eh
Notes: Unassigned

Name: .eu
Notes: Restricted to legal and natural persons in European Union member states. Previously unofficially used for sites in the Basque language, but now .eus is in official use.

Name: .fi
Notes: Registration allowed worldwide, local presence not required.

Name: .fm
Notes: Also unofficially used by FM radio stations, podcasts or related business.

Name: .fr
Notes: Restricted to individuals and companies in European Union, Switzerland, Norway, Iceland and Liechtenstein.

Name: .ga
Notes: Also used as a free domain service to the public.

Name: .ge
Notes: Available for registration for residents of Georgia (unlimited) or for foreign companies via representation of any local legal person (one domain name per registrant).

Name: .gg
Notes: Also unofficially used by video game related websites (see GG (gaming))

Name: .gl
Notes: Previously also unofficially used in Galicia, Spain, but now .gal has been approved for such use and was implemented in mid-2014

Name: .gm
Notes: Domain name should match the domain owners name or trademarks. Common nouns are blocked.

Name: .gn
Notes: A local contact is required

Name: .gp
Notes: Still used for Saint-Barthélemy and Saint-Martin

Name: .gq
Notes: Also used as a free domain service to the public.

Name: .gs
Entity: South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands (United Kingdom)
Explanation: South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands

Name: .gu
Notes: Registry has been closed since 2017.

Name: .hm
Notes: Unused for its intended purposes (islands are uninhabited and government sites instead use .aq); registry open to the public.

Name: .hu
Notes: Citizens of the European Union or entities established by law within the territory of the EU

Name: .id
Notes: Restricted to Indonesian companies (co.id), organisations (or.id), academic (ac.id & sch.id) and citizens (biz.id, my.id & web.id). Second-level domains are becoming available now and opened to general registration on 17 August 2014.

Name: .ie
Notes: In 2002, registration was expanded to include persons or businesses with a "real and substantive" connection with the island of Ireland (including Northern Ireland).

Name: .in
Notes: Under INRegistry since April 2005 (except for gov.in, nic.in, mil.in, ac.in, edu.in, res.in).

Name: .io
Notes: Used unofficially by technology companies, startups, and web applications because IO can be an acronym for input / output that is useful for domain hacks.

Name: .is
Notes: Also unofficially used and marketed as a domain hack (for example it.is, that.is, etc.).

Name: .it
Notes: Restricted to companies and individuals in the European Union.

Name: .jp
Notes: Restricted to individuals or companies with a physical address in Japan.

Name: .kp
Notes: Restricted to companies, organizations, or government entities based in North Korea. Despite this, few domains are actually registered because of internet censorship in North Korea.

Name: .la
Notes: Currently being marketed as the unofficial domain for Los Angeles.

Name: .lb
Notes: Restricted to registration with a company in Lebanon

Name: .li
Notes: Also unofficially used by entities on Long Island, New York or people with the last name Li. In Russian, li can be used to create domain names that mean a verb with a past tense plural ending li .

Name: .lu
Notes: Also unofficially used in Lucerne, Switzerland

Name: .ly
Notes: Used unofficially as a domain hack for words ending in -ly.

Name: .mc
Notes: Only for companies with a trademark registered in Monaco.

Name: .md
Notes: Restricted to individuals or companies with a physical address in Moldova.

Name: .me
Notes: Also unofficially used and marketed as a domain hack (for example love.me, meet.me, etc.).

Name: .mg
Notes: Restricted to registration with a company in Madagascar

Name: .mk
Notes: Restricted to registration with a company in North Macedonia

Name: .ml
Notes: Also used as a free domain service to the public.

Name: .mn
Notes: The second-level domains .gov.mn, .org.mn, and .edu.mn are reserved for special use. See .mn for more information.

Name: .mo
Notes: Registrants must have a registered business in Macau, with the same name as the domain they wish to register.

Name: .ms
Notes: Also unofficially used for Microsoft-related domains.

Name: .my
Notes: Restricted to registration by an individual or company in Malaysia

Name: .nc
Notes: Restricted to companies that have a New Caledonian Business Registration Certificate or individuals living in New Caledonia for at least 6 months.

Name: .nl
Notes: First active country-code domain outside the US.

Name: .no
Notes: Businesses and professionals must be registered as an approved type of organization in the Brønnøysund Register Centre. Individual applicants must be of age (18 years) and be registered in Folkeregisteret. All applicants must have a Norwegian postal address.

Name: .np
Notes: All .np domains are free to register for individuals and registered businesses. Foreign businesses must provide proof of local presence in Nepal.

Name: .nr
Notes: Was previously used as a free domain service to the public as co.nr.

Name: .nu
Notes: Commonly used by Danish, Dutch, and Swedish websites, because in those languages "nu" means "now".

Name: .om
Notes: Registrant must have company or trademark registered in Oman as well as a local administrative contact.

Name: .pa
Notes: Some use in Pennsylvania

Name: .pe
Notes: Also unofficially used for Private Equity related businesses.

Name: .pf
Notes: With Clipperton Island

Name: .pk
Notes: Operated by PKNIC since 1992

Name: .pm
Notes: Restricted to individuals and companies in European Union, Switzerland, Norway, Iceland and Liechtenstein.

Name: .pn
Notes: As a part of a marketing campaign, Lionsgate used the TLD for some (now defunct) sites related to The Hunger Games franchise, presenting it as the "official" country code of the fictional nation of Panem, notable sites included thecapitol.pn and revolution.pn.

Name: .ps
Notes: Jerusalem, West Bank and Gaza Strip.

Name: .re
Notes: Restricted to individuals and companies in European Union, Switzerland, Norway, Iceland and Liechtenstein.

Name: .rs
Notes: See also .срб (.srb in Cyrillic). Also unofficially used for Rust (programming language)-related domains.

Name: .ru
Notes: See also .su, still in use, and .рф, for IDN.

Name: .sa
Notes: Registrant must have a registered trademark in Saudi Arabia matching the domain name to register or provide company incorporation documents of a company in Saudi Arabia or for personal registrations a copy of valid ID. A letter on the official letterhead of your organization addressed to SaudiNIC requesting the domain name registration is also required. Local administrative contact required. 2LD registrations rolled out in 2011.

Name: .sc
Notes: Also unofficially used for Snapchat-related domains.

Name: .sg
Notes: Also unofficially used in the Canton of St. Gallen, Switzerland

Name: .sh
Entity: Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha (United Kingdom)

Name: .sk
Notes: Restricted to Slovak companies, organisations, and citizens.

Name: .sm
Notes: Domain name must be same as company name or trademark.

Name: .sn
Notes: Registration allowed for companies only. Individuals are not allowed to register.

Name: .so
Notes: Relaunched on 1 November 2010.

Name: .ss
Notes: Added to the DNS root zone in February 2019. Registry is not yet available.

Name: .st
Notes: Also unofficially used in South Tyrol (or province of Bozen, see .bz).

Name: .su
Notes: Still in use. Also unofficially used by Student Unions.

Name: .sz
Notes: Registration is restricted to Eswatini organizations with Eswatini Trading Licenses.

Name: .tc
Notes: Also marketed in Turkey. The official abbreviation of 'Türkiye Cumhuriyeti' (Republic of Turkey) is TC.

Name: .td
Notes: Available for registration to entities connected with Chad only.

Name: .tf
Notes: Seldom used. Restricted to individuals and companies in European Union, Switzerland, Norway, Iceland, and Liechtenstein. Domains must be longer than two characters. The domain also sees frequent use for community-run sites related to the video game Team Fortress 2.

Name: .tk
Notes: Also used as a free domain service to the public.

Name: .tl
Notes: Old code .tp has been deactivated since 2015.

Name: .tn
Notes: Currently being marketed as the unofficial domain for Tamil Nadu

Name: .to
Notes: Often used unofficially for Torrent, Turin (Torino in Italian), Toronto, Tokyo, or Tocantins, and also as a domain hack in Slavic languages (to meaning it).

Name: .tr
Notes: .ct.tr and .nc.tr used by Northern Cyprus

Name: .tv
Notes: Used as an abbreviation of television, the domain is currently operated by dotTV, a VeriSign company; the Tuvalu government owns twenty percent of the company.

Name: .tw
Notes: Registration allowed worldwide, local presence not required. In line with ISO 3166-1, IANA's official position is that "TW" is "designated for use to represent Taiwan, Province of China".

Name: .tz
Notes: Must have a presence in Tanzania

Name: .uk
Notes: The ISO 3166-1 code for the United Kingdom is GB. UK is a specially reserved ISO 3166-1 code. However, the creation of the .uk TLD predates the ISO 3166-1 list of ccTLD and is the primary TLD for the United Kingdom.

Name: .us
Notes: Registrants must be United States citizens, residents, or organizations, or a foreign entity with a presence in the United States. Formerly commonly used by U.S. State and local governments, see also .gov TLD.

Name: .uy
Notes: 2LD rollout began on 10 July 2012.

Name: .va
Notes: Limited to the official sites of the Holy See (including those of the Vatican City State).

Name: .ve
Notes: Registration is at the third level.

Name: .wf
Notes: Restricted to individuals and companies in European Union, Switzerland, Norway, Iceland, and Liechtenstein.

Name: .ws
Notes: Marketed for use in general Websites

Name: .ye
Notes: Also unofficially used by Kanye West[citation needed].

Name: .yt
Notes: Restricted to individuals and companies in European Union, Switzerland, Norway, Iceland and Liechtenstein. Also unofficially used for YouTube-related domains.

Name: .za
Notes: .za derives from the Dutch name of the country, even though Dutch is no longer an official language.
